ch.ecma.csta.binding

Class SetAgentState

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • ch.ecma.csta.binding.SetAgentState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class SetAgentState
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Set the state of the specified agent.

    The SetAgentState request has the following parameters:

    SetAgentState Request Parameters
    device Mandatory Specifies the DeviceID for the agent extension. This must be a valid on-PBX station extension for an ACD agent.
    requestedAgentState Mandatory Specifies the requested agent state. The supported values are:
    • loggedOn - Requests that the agent be logged on.
    • loggedOff - Requests that the agent be logged off.
    • notReady - Requests that the agent be placed into the notReady agent state.
    • ready - Requests that the agent be placed into the ready state.
    • workingAfterCall - Requests that the agent be placed into the workingAfterCall state.
    Note that the list of values in this parameter is different from the list of values in the agentState parameter in the Get Agent State service.
    agentID Conditional Specifies the Agent login identifier for the ACD agent. This parameter is mandatory when the requestedAgentState parameter is loggedOn; otherwise it is ignored. An agentID containing a Logical Agents login Identifier can be used to log in a Logical Agent (Expert Agent Selection [EAS]) when paired with the password.
    password Optional Specifies the agent password. It is used when the requestedAgentState is set to loggedon, otherwise it is ignored.
    group Conditional Specifies the ACD agent split to use to log in, log out, or change the agent work mode to "notReady", "ready" or "workingAfterCall". In an Expert Agent Selection (EAS) environment, the group parameter must contain the skill group extension.
    privateData Optional Non-standardized information attached to the request.

    Negative Acknowledgements:

    • operation:invalidDeviceID - Sent if an invalid device ID has been specified or if the the password is wrong when logging in an agent.
    • operation:generic - Sent if an attempt to log in an ACD agent that is already logged in.
    • operation:invalidAgentState - Sent if an attempt to log out an ACD agent who is already logged out, an attempt to log in an ACD agent to a split of which they are not a member, or an attempt to log in an ACD agent with an incorrect password.
    • operation:valueOutOfRange - Sent if the workMode private parameter is not valid for the requestedAgentState or the reasonCode is outside the acceptable range of 0-99.
    • operation:objectNotKnown - Sent if a an invalid on-PBX station was specified for the ACD agent in device.
    • operation:invalidFeature - Sent if the feature is not available for the group, or the enablePending feature is not available for the administered switch version.
    • operation:invalidObjectType - Sent if the reason code is specified, but the workMode is not AUXWORK, or requestedAgentState is not LOGGEDOUT.
    • stateIncompatibility:generic - Sent if a work mode change was requested for a non-ACD agent, or the Agent station is maintenance busy or out of service.
    • stateIncompatibility:invalidObjectState - Sent if the Agent is already logged into another split.
    • systemResourceAvailability:resourceBusy - Sent if an attempt to log in an ACD agent that is currently on a call.
    • systemResourceAvailability:generic - Sent if the request cannot be completed due to lack of available switch resources.
    • operation:securityViolation - Sent if the user was not authorized to control the specified device.
    • operation:generic - Sent if a logic error occurred in the code.
    • unspecified - Sent if an implementation specific error occurred.
    Version:
